Ko zna? Možda æeš postati
zapovednik bataljona?

685
01:14:54,167 --> 01:14:55,964
Imaj ovo na umu:

686
01:14:57,537 --> 01:15:02,406
Sin Jong-mana, Min-seok, æe rasti bez oca, bas kao mi...

687
01:15:02,476 --> 01:15:06,003
i nositi mržnju prema nama.

688
01:15:06,513 --> 01:15:07,502
Prestani. 

689
01:15:07,581 --> 01:15:12,177
Da si me poslušao,
on ne bi bio mrtav!

690
01:15:13,820 --> 01:15:15,287
Da li znas zbog èega je umro?

691
01:15:15,689 --> 01:15:20,683
Da li znaš šta si ti radio dok je on umirao?

692
01:15:20,994 --> 01:15:24,486
Šta ti vredi odlikovanje
kada ljudi ginu zbog njega?

693
01:15:26,933 --> 01:15:27,922
Prekini.

694
01:16:14,781 --> 01:16:15,770
Koji ðavo...

695
01:16:24,558 --> 01:16:27,026
Ovde Galeb 1.

696
01:16:27,093 --> 01:16:31,462
Komunisti
su pobili preko 100 seljaka tokom povlaèenja.

697
01:16:31,531 --> 01:16:32,520
Primljeno.

698
01:16:38,271 --> 01:16:40,865
Javi glavnoj komandi.

699
01:16:42,475 --> 01:16:44,739
Pobrinimo se za tela.

700
01:17:09,336 --> 01:17:11,998
Pomozite mi. Molim vas,
naðite moju majku.

701
01:17:12,205 --> 01:17:15,197
Molim vas, naðite moju majku.

702
01:17:15,942 --> 01:17:18,843
Ne plaèi, pomoæi æu ti.

703
01:17:33,159 --> 01:17:34,456
Bolnièar!

704
01:17:34,527 --> 01:17:35,858
Bolnièar!

705
01:17:37,430 --> 01:17:40,160
Èak su postavili zamke!

706
01:17:44,738 --> 01:17:47,206
Nemojte da ijedan skot ostane živ!

707
01:18:15,568 --> 01:18:16,865
Umri!

708
01:18:23,410 --> 01:18:26,607
Prljavi pione amerièkog imperijalizma!

709
01:18:33,219 --> 01:18:35,414
Molim te, nemoj me ubiti!

710
01:19:18,431 --> 01:19:21,594
Postrojite ih uza zid!

711
01:20:33,306 --> 01:20:35,968
- Ti!
- Predajem se!

712
01:20:36,709 --> 01:20:39,473
- Koliko ih ima tamo?
- Petorica.

713
01:20:39,546 --> 01:20:42,674
I oni æe izaæi. Molim
vas, nemojte nas ubiti!

714
01:20:42,749 --> 01:20:44,307
Vi ste ih ubili, zar ne?

715
01:20:44,384 --> 01:20:47,581
Ne, bili su mrtvi kad smo došli.

716
01:20:47,654 --> 01:20:49,588
Još jedna laž i mrtav si,
jasno?

717
01:20:49,656 --> 01:20:51,089
Vi ste ih ubili?

718
01:20:51,224 --> 01:20:52,657
Ne pucaj!

719
01:20:52,725 --> 01:20:54,488
Nemoj me lagati!

720
01:20:54,761 --> 01:20:57,059
Molim te!

721
01:21:02,602 --> 01:21:03,728
Jung-seok!

722
01:21:04,537 --> 01:21:05,799
Jin-seok!

723
01:21:07,640 --> 01:21:08,902
Šta se dogodilo?

724
01:21:10,243 --> 01:21:14,179
Prisilili su me da pristupim vojsci Severne Koreje,
u protivnom bi me ubili.

725
01:21:16,015 --> 01:21:18,575
Sad je u redu, ne plaèi.

726
01:21:22,889 --> 01:21:24,413
Popij ovo.

727
01:21:25,758 --> 01:21:26,918
Da predam izveštaj?

728
01:21:30,563 --> 01:21:31,894
Jin-tae!

729
01:21:32,332 --> 01:21:34,857
Javi da su svi
neprijatelji ubijeni u borbi.

730
01:21:34,934 --> 01:21:37,459
- O èemu govoriš?
- Oni su dodatni teret.

731
01:21:37,537 --> 01:21:41,132
To je Jung-seok!
Bio ti je kao brat!

732
01:21:41,207 --> 01:21:43,402
Sada vidim samo komunistu.

733
01:21:43,476 --> 01:21:46,843
Ja sam Jung-seok, tvoj prijatelj.

734
01:21:46,913 --> 01:21:50,940
Moji prijatelji ne ubijaju naše ljude.

735
01:21:54,220 --> 01:21:55,551
Stanite na stranu!

736
01:21:55,622 --> 01:21:57,715
Mi nismo komunisti!

737
01:21:57,790 --> 01:21:59,917
Prisilili su ga da doðe ovamo!

738
01:21:59,993 --> 01:22:01,119
Odmakni se.

739
01:22:01,194 --> 01:22:02,286
Vi ste ih ubili?

740
01:22:02,362 --> 01:22:04,455
Nismo! Stvarno!

741
01:22:04,530 --> 01:22:06,191
Kaže da nisu!

742
01:22:06,266 --> 01:22:09,929
- Ne verujem komunistima.
- Oni su životinje!

743
01:22:12,171 --> 01:22:15,766
Molim te, nemoj me ubiti!

744
01:22:15,842 --> 01:22:17,173
Ne diraj me!

745
01:22:20,980 --> 01:22:22,174
Na kolena!

746
01:22:23,116 --> 01:22:25,710
- Svinjo prljava!
- Nemoj me ubiti!

747
01:22:28,488 --> 01:22:32,982
Samo napred, a ja æu
prijaviti da si ubio nenaoružane vojnike.

748
01:22:33,426 --> 01:22:37,726
Nisi ništa bolji od komunista!

749
01:22:37,797 --> 01:22:40,459
Vi ste svi poludeli! To su taoci!

750
01:22:40,533 --> 01:22:44,025
Video si šta su uradili! To su životinje!

751
01:22:44,103 --> 01:22:46,503
If we kill them, we are animals, too.

752
01:22:46,572 --> 01:22:48,665
It was them who started the war!

753
01:22:48,741 --> 01:22:53,303
We're the same. No better, no worse!

754
01:22:53,680 --> 01:22:56,877
Okay, kill them. Shoot.

755
01:22:56,950 --> 01:23:00,977
What are you waiting for? Shoot!

756
01:23:07,093 --> 01:23:09,721
Today's your lucky day!

757
01:23:19,939 --> 01:23:22,601
Hye-San-Jin, North Korea - November 1950

758
01:23:33,052 --> 01:23:34,713
Yong-seok.

759
01:23:36,789 --> 01:23:38,120
Jin-seok!

760
01:23:38,624 --> 01:23:39,955
Take it.

761
01:23:42,562 --> 01:23:45,122
Boys! Have some.

762
01:23:51,471 --> 01:23:52,438
Are you okay?

763
01:23:52,505 --> 01:23:53,665
I feel fine.

764
01:23:59,579 --> 01:24:00,705
Take your time.

765
01:24:03,116 --> 01:24:06,552
I filed a report about you
with the regimental office.

766
01:24:06,619 --> 01:24:08,143
Thanks a lot.

767
01:24:10,923 --> 01:24:14,552
Jin-tae is a totally different person.

768
01:24:14,827 --> 01:24:16,920
He's so changed.

769
01:24:17,897 --> 01:24:21,765
Just before I left,
I met your mom and Young-shin.

770
01:24:22,568 --> 01:24:23,933
Really?

771
01:24:24,537 --> 01:24:26,368
How are they?
When did they come back home?

772
01:24:26,439 --> 01:24:28,236
Just after you were drafted.

773
01:24:28,307 --> 01:24:33,244
She wanted to be home
in case you came back.

774
01:24:33,479 --> 01:24:37,313
She asked people about you.

775
01:24:38,551 --> 01:24:43,545
Whenever she saw me, she cried.
I reminded her of you two.

776
01:24:47,260 --> 01:24:48,693
And the noodle stand?

777
01:24:48,861 --> 01:24:50,260
Actually...

778
01:24:51,397 --> 01:24:53,024
she isn't well.

779
01:24:53,099 --> 01:24:54,566
What's wrong?

780
01:24:55,935 --> 01:24:57,232
Is she very ill?

781
01:24:57,303 --> 01:24:59,203
I don't know exactly...

782
01:24:59,272 --> 01:25:03,936
but she couldn't move well.

783
01:25:04,077 --> 01:25:08,070
Young-shin was having a hard time...

784
01:25:08,147 --> 01:25:10,638
Iooking after everyone.

785
01:25:10,750 --> 01:25:13,378
The commies wouldn't let her run the stand.

786
01:25:13,453 --> 01:25:16,980
She attends rallies all day long.

787
01:25:17,056 --> 01:25:19,547
It's the only way to get food.

788
01:25:20,426 --> 01:25:22,417
Don't worry, though.

789
01:25:22,662 --> 01:25:26,860
Things may be getting better.

790
01:25:29,769 --> 01:25:34,570
I miss the noodles your mom cooks.

791
01:25:40,213 --> 01:25:43,239
The loser doesn't eat for two days!

792
01:25:45,118 --> 01:25:47,211
Bastards!

793
01:25:47,887 --> 01:25:49,115
Do it right!

794
01:25:49,188 --> 01:25:52,214
Kill him! Kill him!

795
01:25:52,291 --> 01:25:53,883
Do it right, bastards!

796
01:25:53,960 --> 01:25:57,418
Two days aren't bad enough?
You want five?

797
01:25:57,497 --> 01:26:00,193
You ain't hungry?

798
01:26:05,671 --> 01:26:07,263
You see now?

799
01:26:12,211 --> 01:26:16,375
Think of him as a South Korean pig.

800
01:26:18,251 --> 01:26:21,015
Fight until one gets knocked out.

801
01:26:21,087 --> 01:26:25,490
If not, I'll kill both of you. You got it?

802
01:26:25,625 --> 01:26:28,059
Who's going to be the damn South Korean?

803
01:26:29,962 --> 01:26:31,623
You do it!

804
01:26:31,697 --> 01:26:33,824
You don't need to.

805
01:26:35,535 --> 01:26:38,368
You don't have to. It's you and me now.

806
01:26:38,437 --> 01:26:41,565
- What the hell are you doing?
- Isn't this a game?

807
01:26:41,641 --> 01:26:44,132
Fight, or you'll die of starvation.

808
01:26:44,210 --> 01:26:45,575
Stop it!

809
01:26:45,645 --> 01:26:49,604
Come on, son of a bitch!

810
01:26:55,688 --> 01:26:58,782
There you go, that's the way.

811
01:27:13,839 --> 01:27:15,067
We're not done yet!

812
01:27:29,989 --> 01:27:33,948
We fight until one of us can't get up!

813
01:28:07,960 --> 01:28:11,521
- You're killing him.
- Let go!

814
01:28:14,700 --> 01:28:18,101
Anyone tries to stop me, I'll kill you, too!

815
01:28:18,971 --> 01:28:22,634
Get up, or you'll starve to death!

816
01:28:22,708 --> 01:28:25,734
Fight, or you're dead.

817
01:28:26,078 --> 01:28:27,670
Do you want to die?

818
01:28:27,747 --> 01:28:30,181
I said, fight, you pig!

819
01:28:31,884 --> 01:28:33,545
I said, fight, you pig!

820
01:29:14,126 --> 01:29:19,029
<i>Many of our brave soldiers sacrificed
their lives for their country.</i>

821
01:29:19,098 --> 01:29:23,626
<i>And the long-awaited victory is very close.</i>

822
01:29:23,703 --> 01:29:26,467
- Just stay still!
- It hurts!

823
01:29:26,539 --> 01:29:28,200
Stay still! It's supposed to hurt.

824
01:29:28,274 --> 01:29:30,003
When the hell can we go home?

825
01:29:33,312 --> 01:29:38,306
<i>And General MacArthur has ordered
U.N. Forces to advance to the North.</i>

826
01:29:38,617 --> 01:29:42,348
<i>The victory is ours.</i>

827
01:29:42,555 --> 01:29:44,079
Victory!

828
01:30:00,606 --> 01:30:03,666
We kicked their asses!

829
01:30:03,909 --> 01:30:07,470
It looks like the war may be over soon.

830
01:30:07,546 --> 01:30:10,379
I wouldn't be so sure.
I heard the Chinese will back the North.

831
01:30:10,449 --> 01:30:13,782
That's just commie propaganda.

832
01:30:15,187 --> 01:30:17,348
Uncle Yang, what do you think?

833
01:30:17,423 --> 01:30:20,358
The Sunspot...

834
01:30:20,426 --> 01:30:25,022
and Great Bear are losing energy now...

835
01:30:25,097 --> 01:30:28,260
and we will be home before the New Year.

836
01:30:28,334 --> 01:30:31,861
- You really sure this time?
- What the hell!

837
01:30:33,305 --> 01:30:35,330
Okay, I believe you.

838
01:30:35,708 --> 01:30:36,766
Sergeant Lee!

839
01:30:38,043 --> 01:30:39,442
Sergeant Lee!

840
01:30:40,479 --> 01:30:42,140
Jin-tae, congratulations!

841
01:30:43,215 --> 01:30:46,241
He'll get the Medal of Honor!

842
01:30:49,889 --> 01:30:52,289
I was hoping you would get it.
Congratulations!

843
01:30:52,358 --> 01:30:55,259
You got it for catching the captain alive.

844
01:30:55,327 --> 01:30:56,988
The commander is really pleased.

845
01:30:58,030 --> 01:31:01,591
- What is the Medal of Honor?
- You idiot!

846
01:31:01,667 --> 01:31:04,135
Any time "honor" is in
the medal's name, it's good.

847
01:31:04,203 --> 01:31:09,163
Tomorrow, the commander
will award it himself.

848
01:31:10,576 --> 01:31:13,511
Let's give him a big hand!

849
01:31:17,750 --> 01:31:19,684
We need to celebrate!

850
01:31:19,752 --> 01:31:24,246
Sergeant Lee, you can be a soldier forever.

851
01:31:30,763 --> 01:31:32,196
Jin-seok!

852
01:31:33,499 --> 01:31:35,126
Let's talk.

853
01:31:35,301 --> 01:31:38,361
Make it short. I'm on duty.

854
01:31:38,971 --> 01:31:40,734
You can go home soon.

855
01:31:40,940 --> 01:31:44,774
Then go back to school right away.
You missed a lot.

856
01:31:44,844 --> 01:31:49,042
You're the one that needs to go home.
You're sick.

857
01:31:49,348 --> 01:31:50,508
I'm not going home.

858
01:31:51,550 --> 01:31:53,575
You'll do what I say.

859
01:31:53,652 --> 01:31:56,746
- I don't want anything from you.
- Listen to me.

860
01:31:57,790 --> 01:31:59,815
What's wrong with you?

861
01:32:00,259 --> 01:32:02,693
I worked my ass off for that medal!

862
01:32:03,028 --> 01:32:05,189
This is a great chance for us!

863
01:32:05,264 --> 01:32:07,528
For you, not for me.

864
01:32:08,000 --> 01:32:10,025
Have you thought about
what the medal means?

865
01:32:10,102 --> 01:32:14,004
I don't care. I needed one to send you home.

866
01:32:14,073 --> 01:32:18,703
That medal cost Yong-man his life!
I won't go.

867
01:32:18,777 --> 01:32:22,269
- You have to go to college!
- What good is college now?

868
01:32:22,348 --> 01:32:24,646
I hate you and everything you stand for.

869
01:32:24,717 --> 01:32:28,209
- Don't tell me what to do.
- Do you really mean that?

870
01:32:28,287 --> 01:32:31,654
I will make my own decisions.
Don't tell me what to do.

871
01:32:31,724 --> 01:32:34,716
Do you really want one of us to die?

872
01:32:34,793 --> 01:32:37,261
Then you go home instead!

873
01:32:37,329 --> 01:32:39,763
What did I risk my life for?

874
01:32:39,832 --> 01:32:41,629
I didn't ask you to!

875
01:32:50,576 --> 01:32:54,512
I want you to go home alive.

876
01:32:55,080 --> 01:32:59,039
I also want to go home, you know.

877
01:32:59,652 --> 01:33:04,646
But you are our family's hopes and dreams!

878
01:33:04,924 --> 01:33:09,861
I never regretted giving up school
and shining shoes for you.

879
01:33:11,530 --> 01:33:15,990
Mom happily broke her back for you.

880
01:33:16,068 --> 01:33:18,662
Do you know our sacrifices?

881
01:33:18,737 --> 01:33:22,104
Of course I do. I know all of it.

882
01:33:22,975 --> 01:33:25,273
Why am I the only one you think about?

883
01:33:25,344 --> 01:33:29,804
If you had thought about Young-shin
and Yong-man, you couldn't have done it.

884
01:33:31,884 --> 01:33:35,718
I don't care what you think,
as long as you can go home.

885
01:33:46,565 --> 01:33:48,556
The command post will leave first.

886
01:33:48,634 --> 01:33:51,467
Take the classified documents
and burn the others.

887
01:33:51,537 --> 01:33:52,834
Yes, sir!

888
01:33:52,905 --> 01:33:54,338
One more telegram.

889
01:33:54,406 --> 01:33:57,842
"Retreat to second rendezvous point.
Date of order: 0900 hours."

890
01:33:57,910 --> 01:34:00,640
Regiments 12, 13 and 25
are already retreating.

891
01:34:00,713 --> 01:34:02,738
The U.S. Army is retreating, too.

892
01:34:02,815 --> 01:34:05,045
How many Chinese reinforcements
are coming?

893
01:34:05,117 --> 01:34:07,176
For Woon-san city alone, at least 100,000.

894
01:34:07,252 --> 01:34:08,981
They'll fire on us any minute, sir.

895
01:34:21,567 --> 01:34:24,092
Hurry, they're getting close.

896
01:34:24,169 --> 01:34:27,070
Sergeant Lee, what are you doing?

897
01:34:28,173 --> 01:34:30,937
What the hell?
Everything was going so well.

898
01:34:31,010 --> 01:34:34,446
We'll never get home before New Year!

899
01:34:34,513 --> 01:34:37,107
We're just going to leave? How stupid!

900
01:34:37,182 --> 01:34:40,174
Shouldn't we die here?

901
01:34:40,252 --> 01:34:42,948
This is wrong! We should be fighting.

902
01:34:43,022 --> 01:34:45,991
Stop bitching and hurry up!

903
01:34:46,625 --> 01:34:50,493
I wanted to believe your shit,
but look at this!

904
01:35:22,895 --> 01:35:24,522
Get the jeep ready!

905
01:35:30,235 --> 01:35:32,795
How far are we going to carry them?

906
01:35:47,352 --> 01:35:48,683
Don't move!

907
01:35:57,930 --> 01:35:59,830
Get him!

908
01:36:13,212 --> 01:36:16,807
- Sergeant Huh!
- I'm all right. Retreat.

909
01:36:17,149 --> 01:36:18,173
Medic!

910
01:36:21,820 --> 01:36:23,014
Sergeant Huh!

911
01:36:25,023 --> 01:36:26,854
Bastards!

912
01:36:28,127 --> 01:36:30,527
Where's my arm?

913
01:36:38,737 --> 01:36:41,968
- Stay back!
- Put the dagger away!

914
01:36:42,040 --> 01:36:43,234
I'll kill him!

915
01:36:44,076 --> 01:36:45,441
Kill them all!

916
01:36:46,345 --> 01:36:49,314
Don't come any closer.

917
01:36:58,457 --> 01:36:59,788
Hurry, just kill them!

918
01:36:59,858 --> 01:37:01,485
Step away.

919
01:37:02,361 --> 01:37:05,489
If you come any closer, this bastard is dead!

920
01:37:20,412 --> 01:37:21,436
No!

921
01:37:26,218 --> 01:37:29,847
Yong-seok, come on!

922
01:37:50,642 --> 01:37:52,007
Are you crazy?

923
01:37:52,744 --> 01:37:57,681
How could you?
How could you kill Yong-seok?

924
01:37:58,717 --> 01:38:00,947
You're crazy! You're mad!

925
01:38:07,392 --> 01:38:09,792
Stop this!

926
01:38:12,164 --> 01:38:16,965
Bring him back! You're a murderer!

927
01:38:22,241 --> 01:38:27,201
What the hell are you doing?
You two knock it off!

928
01:38:33,986 --> 01:38:35,749
We've got to get out of here!

929
01:38:46,798 --> 01:38:51,735
How come we're retreating without fighting?

930
01:39:19,531 --> 01:39:22,728
Jang-Dan, near the 38th parallel
December 1950

931
01:39:59,404 --> 01:40:01,201
"Staff Sergeant Lee Jin-tae.

932
01:40:01,273 --> 01:40:05,835
"You're awarded the Medal of Honor
for your actions in Pyongyang...

933
01:40:05,911 --> 01:40:10,314
"your remarkable bravery
and actions at many battles...

934
01:40:10,382 --> 01:40:12,350
"and for going beyond the call of duty.

935
01:40:12,417 --> 01:40:16,080
"December 1, 1950.
President Rhee Syngman."

936
01:40:28,000 --> 01:40:29,297
Staff Sergeant Lee Jin-tae!

937
01:40:29,368 --> 01:40:31,563
Congratulations, you've finally made it!

938
01:40:31,636 --> 01:40:32,625
Thank you.

939
01:40:32,704 --> 01:40:36,834
This should have been
a formal occasion. Sorry.

940
01:40:39,678 --> 01:40:44,240
1st Battalion,
proceed to the third rendezvous site.

941
01:40:44,316 --> 01:40:49,185
2nd, 3rd and 4th Battalions
to the fifth rendezvous point.

942
01:40:49,254 --> 01:40:52,417
Be at your locations
by 1800 hours tomorrow.

943
01:40:52,491 --> 01:40:57,360
All forces will be reorganized there.
Dismissed.

944
01:40:58,397 --> 01:41:01,161
See you at the next site.

945
01:41:04,870 --> 01:41:07,737
- Sir, may I have a word with you?
- Go ahead.

946
01:41:07,806 --> 01:41:10,070
Sir, it's about my younger brother.

947
01:41:10,142 --> 01:41:15,102
I'll make the official request
with the division commander.

948
01:41:15,180 --> 01:41:17,375
Thank you, sir.

949
01:41:17,449 --> 01:41:19,849
I'm afraid we'll be pushed down to Seoul.

950
01:41:19,918 --> 01:41:23,012
I'm afraid we're going further
to the south, across Nakdong.

951
01:41:23,088 --> 01:41:25,079
You know where Jin-seok is?

952
01:41:25,157 --> 01:41:27,216
He left a minute ago.

953
01:41:27,626 --> 01:41:29,389
- By himself?
- Yeah.

954
01:41:29,494 --> 01:41:34,397
He said he was going
to see your mom. She is sick.

955
01:42:23,215 --> 01:42:24,580
Mom!

956
01:42:41,032 --> 01:42:42,192
Jin-seok!

957
01:42:47,839 --> 01:42:48,999
Young-shin!

958
01:42:49,541 --> 01:42:51,065
Thank God.

959
01:42:57,616 --> 01:43:02,019
You're alive. This isn't a dream, is it?

960
01:43:07,092 --> 01:43:08,957
I'm on my way to reassemble.

961
01:43:09,027 --> 01:43:13,361
I ran into Yong-seok. He said Mom is sick.

962
01:43:13,498 --> 01:43:16,592
She's feeling much better now.
She's back at work.

963
01:43:17,335 --> 01:43:19,064
How is Jin-tae?

964
01:43:20,338 --> 01:43:22,568
Why didn't he come?

965
01:43:22,641 --> 01:43:26,077
He's fine. He's really busy right now.

966
01:43:27,212 --> 01:43:28,873
That's good.

967
01:43:29,214 --> 01:43:31,910
Mother is so worried.

968
01:43:38,123 --> 01:43:40,114
Are you Kim Young-shin?

969
01:43:40,192 --> 01:43:41,420
Yes, I am. Why?

970
01:43:41,493 --> 01:43:43,825
Come with me. You're under investigation.

971
01:43:43,895 --> 01:43:45,419
For what?

972
01:43:45,864 --> 01:43:49,265
- What?
- Who the hell are you?

973
01:43:49,334 --> 01:43:51,894
- Tell me what this is about.
- Step away!

974
01:43:53,138 --> 01:43:54,628
Stop!

975
01:43:54,706 --> 01:43:57,266
Shoot, if you dare. Put her on.

976
01:43:57,342 --> 01:44:00,971
Take the son of a bitch, too!
Check if he's a communist.

977
01:44:01,213 --> 01:44:06,207
Young-guk, go home! Don't follow me!

978
01:44:22,834 --> 01:44:24,267
Get off!

979
01:44:33,645 --> 01:44:34,839
What is this place?

980
01:44:34,913 --> 01:44:37,848
It's where we investigate commies
like Young-shin!

981
01:44:37,916 --> 01:44:39,713
You're making a mistake.

982
01:44:39,784 --> 01:44:41,843
We'll see about that.

983
01:44:41,920 --> 01:44:43,353
Get in there!

984
01:44:57,402 --> 01:45:00,235
Lee Jung-ja, Jung Kook-sup,
Kim Young-shin.

985
01:45:00,772 --> 01:45:02,000
Get up!

986
01:45:15,754 --> 01:45:16,880
Aim!

987
01:45:20,525 --> 01:45:22,891
Don't even think about it.

988
01:45:23,595 --> 01:45:25,290
Let's not hurt each other.

989
01:45:27,832 --> 01:45:29,129
Get up, Young-shin.

990
01:45:30,468 --> 01:45:31,867
Jin-tae...

991
01:45:31,936 --> 01:45:33,631
Where is Jin-seok?

992
01:45:34,839 --> 01:45:37,364
He was taken into the front building.

993
01:45:37,442 --> 01:45:39,034
What's going on?

994
01:45:41,012 --> 01:45:45,210
They just said I was under investigation
and took me here.

995
01:45:45,283 --> 01:45:48,377
We're executing traitors
according to the law.

996
01:45:48,453 --> 01:45:51,616
I don't care what you're doing.
I'm taking her.

997
01:45:51,690 --> 01:45:54,158
- Then you're a commie, too!
- I don't think so!

998
01:45:54,225 --> 01:45:59,128
Kim Young-shin, 23, signed up for the
Communist Party on June 23.

999
01:45:59,197 --> 01:46:01,188
We have her signature!

1000
01:46:01,266 --> 01:46:04,565
I did it only for food.
I didn't know what it was!

1001
01:46:04,636 --> 01:46:08,037
She worked for
the Communist Party 35 times...

1002
01:46:08,106 --> 01:46:10,574
and participated in numerous
communist rallies!

1003
01:46:10,642 --> 01:46:14,738
We were starving.
I have to get food somehow!

1004
01:46:14,813 --> 01:46:18,977
The South Korean government
gave us nothing!

1005
01:46:19,050 --> 01:46:21,678
Shut up. You step away.

1006
01:46:21,753 --> 01:46:24,415
- Don't be stupid.
- You're dead, too.

1007
01:46:24,856 --> 01:46:26,824
Touch her, you're all dead!

1008
01:46:26,891 --> 01:46:28,950
This is the last warning. Step aside.

1009
01:46:29,027 --> 01:46:30,119
Don't move...

1010
01:46:32,931 --> 01:46:34,990
or you won't walk out of here in one piece.

1011
01:46:35,066 --> 01:46:37,193
Do you know what you are doing?

1012
01:46:37,268 --> 01:46:40,135
I'm stopping you
from killing innocent people.

1013
01:46:40,205 --> 01:46:41,695
Get her out of here!

1014
01:46:41,773 --> 01:46:43,934
You want to save a whore?

1015
01:46:44,008 --> 01:46:46,738
She was with every single
North Korean officer!

1016
01:46:46,811 --> 01:46:48,438
Shut your mouth, or I'll blow it off!

1017
01:46:48,513 --> 01:46:51,209
That's why she isn't fleeing.

1018
01:46:51,983 --> 01:46:52,972
That's not true.

1019
01:46:53,051 --> 01:46:55,178
There's no use in denying it.

1020
01:46:55,253 --> 01:46:58,120
- No, that's a lie.
- Go now!

1021
01:46:58,189 --> 01:47:03,183
Last warning. If you take her out of here,
you two are commies, too.

1022
01:47:04,062 --> 01:47:07,964
Jin-tae, believe me.

1023
01:47:08,032 --> 01:47:11,900
Get the hell out of here!

1024
01:48:42,360 --> 01:48:43,952
Young-shin!

1025
01:48:50,268 --> 01:48:52,395
Young-shin, hold on!

1026
01:49:02,347 --> 01:49:06,374
You still have the handkerchief.

1027
01:49:06,851 --> 01:49:09,149
You don't know how much I missed you...

1028
01:49:09,687 --> 01:49:12,087
how long I waited for you.

1029
01:49:14,292 --> 01:49:19,025
I didn't do anything shameful.

1030
01:49:19,430 --> 01:49:21,796
Believe me.

1031
01:49:22,600 --> 01:49:23,999
Young-shin!

1032
01:49:26,571 --> 01:49:28,801
I can't die now.

1033
01:49:30,842 --> 01:49:34,107
How can I die now?

1034
01:49:34,212 --> 01:49:36,510
My young siblings...

1035
01:50:57,428 --> 01:51:00,022
Why did you question her?

1036
01:51:01,599 --> 01:51:03,658
You're the one who killed her.

1037
01:51:04,035 --> 01:51:07,994
You killed Young-shin.

1038
01:51:08,439 --> 01:51:09,463
You're responsible.

1039
01:51:09,540 --> 01:51:14,500
You killed her, you murderer...

1040
01:51:14,679 --> 01:51:17,978
You shot members
of the Anti-Communist Federation?

1041
01:51:18,049 --> 01:51:22,486
The Medal of Honor doesn't give you
the right to shoot anyone.

1042
01:51:23,021 --> 01:51:27,788
How can we fight this war
with screwups like you?

1043
01:51:27,859 --> 01:51:30,794
Are you able to contact
headquarters or not?

1044
01:51:30,862 --> 01:51:33,456
I'm still trying, sir.

1045
01:51:33,531 --> 01:51:37,297
How can we hold out for 72 hours
with these losers?

1046
01:51:37,869 --> 01:51:39,928
Send my brother home!

1047
01:51:41,739 --> 01:51:45,505
My former commander promised to.

1048
01:51:45,576 --> 01:51:47,874
What kind of bullshit is this?

1049
01:51:48,146 --> 01:51:52,549
You earn a damn medal
and your brother is discharged?

1050
01:51:52,617 --> 01:51:54,551
You only have to report it.

1051
01:51:54,619 --> 01:51:56,109
I don't believe this!

1052
01:51:56,187 --> 01:52:00,817
I don't give a shit what he promised you!

1053
01:52:00,892 --> 01:52:04,123
You think this is a business deal
or something?

1054
01:52:04,595 --> 01:52:06,586
He made the offer.

1055
01:52:06,664 --> 01:52:11,499
How dare you talk back?
Think of what you've done!

1056
01:52:11,569 --> 01:52:16,006
Lock him up! How could they give
someone like him a medal?

1057
01:52:16,074 --> 01:52:18,872
Urgent message from 1st Company!

1058
01:52:18,976 --> 01:52:21,001
Put him in the cell!

1059
01:52:35,326 --> 01:52:38,523
I don't give a shit about the order.
Just retreat!

1060
01:52:40,431 --> 01:52:44,060
I'll take responsibility.
All companies, retreat!

1061
01:52:44,635 --> 01:52:45,932
Goddamn!

1062
01:52:46,204 --> 01:52:47,535
Open the cell.

1063
01:52:47,605 --> 01:52:49,095
You're crazy!

1064
01:52:49,607 --> 01:52:50,869
Give the order.

1065
01:52:50,942 --> 01:52:53,536
Those commies will kill you first.

1066
01:52:53,845 --> 01:52:55,608
I only want my brother out.

1067
01:52:55,680 --> 01:52:58,774
Not until we finish
examining your heads first.

1068
01:53:01,085 --> 01:53:04,680
Give the order. Now!

1069
01:53:06,057 --> 01:53:08,389
One more thing. The hostages...

1070
01:53:09,260 --> 01:53:11,091
Burn them!

1071
01:53:15,333 --> 01:53:17,460
- Change the order!
- Put the gun away.

1072
01:53:17,535 --> 01:53:20,561
- I said, change the order!
- This is an order. Remove the gun.

1073
01:53:20,638 --> 01:53:21,935
Change the order!

1074
01:53:22,840 --> 01:53:25,934
Order to burn the hostage cells confirmed!

1075
01:56:20,618 --> 01:56:24,315
Military Hospital, Tae-Jeon, South Korea
July 1951

1076
01:56:35,232 --> 01:56:36,665
Jin-seok!

1077
01:56:40,471 --> 01:56:42,098
You look well.

1078
01:56:42,506 --> 01:56:44,531
Thanks. You saved my life.

1079
01:56:44,909 --> 01:56:48,640
I thought I was dead in that cell.

1080
01:56:48,746 --> 01:56:53,649
I did, too, when you got shot
as we were coming out.

1081
01:56:54,018 --> 01:56:56,145
Someone up there likes you.

1082
01:56:56,220 --> 01:56:58,711
- When do you get out of here?
- Next week.

1083
01:56:58,789 --> 01:57:03,692
How nice to be discharged.

1084
01:57:03,761 --> 01:57:07,356
I bet your mom needs your help.

1085
01:57:09,233 --> 01:57:11,997
This damn war should be over.

1086
01:57:12,069 --> 01:57:15,835
The battle around the 38th parallel
is still bloody.

1087
01:57:15,906 --> 01:57:19,000
So many lives are lost every day...

1088
01:57:19,076 --> 01:57:22,341
fighting over more land.

1089
01:57:24,248 --> 01:57:26,978
I bought them on my way.

1090
01:57:28,486 --> 01:57:31,455
Thank you again.

1091
01:57:31,522 --> 01:57:35,549
And your brother sent this letter home...

1092
01:57:35,626 --> 01:57:39,995
but it was returned to the camp.

1093
01:57:40,064 --> 01:57:41,656
You keep this.

1094
01:57:44,535 --> 01:57:49,495
I doubt he retreated then.
I've searched everywhere, but...

1095
01:57:49,573 --> 01:57:51,040
I don't want to know.

1096
01:57:51,742 --> 01:57:53,209
I don't care.

1097
01:57:53,411 --> 01:57:57,108
PFC Lee Jin-seok!
You're wanted in the counseling room.

1098
01:57:57,181 --> 01:57:59,081
Thank you.

1099
01:58:07,558 --> 01:58:10,254
Our decorated hero...

1100
01:58:10,795 --> 01:58:14,356
turned into a communist.

1101
01:58:14,698 --> 01:58:18,896
It's a serious problem for us
and a good propaganda tool for them.

1102
01:58:18,969 --> 01:58:21,233
At first, we didn't believe it.

1103
01:58:21,305 --> 01:58:23,967
But his fiancÃ©e
was executed as a communist.

1104
01:58:24,041 --> 01:58:25,975
That must have affected him.

1105
01:58:26,043 --> 01:58:29,274
He doesn't know what communism
or democracy is.

1106
01:58:29,346 --> 01:58:31,814
Then how come he turned
into a communist?

1107
01:58:31,882 --> 01:58:35,875
He wouldn't have done this
if he had thought of his family.

1108
01:58:35,953 --> 01:58:37,944
I suppose there must be a reason.

1109
01:58:38,022 --> 01:58:42,288
You, too, are a suspect
unless you give us a good explanation.

1110
01:58:42,359 --> 01:58:44,884
I don't care about Jin-tae anymore.

1111
01:58:46,864 --> 01:58:50,891
The Jin-tae I knew was just
an innocent shoeshine boy...

1112
01:58:50,968 --> 01:58:54,699
who loved his family, especially his brother.

1113
01:58:54,772 --> 01:58:58,139
The decorated man leading Flag Unit...

1114
01:58:58,209 --> 01:58:59,733
is not my brother.

1115
01:59:02,513 --> 01:59:06,108
What happened to Jin-tae?
I was questioned, too.

1116
01:59:06,183 --> 01:59:07,912
Did you have lunch?

1117
01:59:08,285 --> 01:59:10,310
How can you eat right now?

1118
01:59:10,421 --> 01:59:15,017
I can't believe it.
How could Jin-tae become a communist?

1119
01:59:15,092 --> 01:59:17,424
He was probably devastated...

1120
01:59:17,495 --> 01:59:21,488
after seeing his fiancÃ©e shot to death.

1121
01:59:21,565 --> 01:59:24,125
He must have thought
you were killed in the fire.

1122
01:59:24,201 --> 01:59:26,795
He loved you so much.

1123
01:59:27,771 --> 01:59:30,103
I don't care about him.

1124
01:59:30,808 --> 01:59:32,867
His only concerns
are for medals and promotions.

1125
01:59:32,943 --> 01:59:35,844
Maybe the commies offered him
a better post.

1126
01:59:35,913 --> 01:59:38,677
I don't even care if he dies.

1127
01:59:38,749 --> 01:59:41,741
Don't speak to me about him ever again.
Do you understand?

1128
02:00:19,156 --> 02:00:21,522
<i>Dear Mother, I miss you every day.</i>

1129
02:00:22,459 --> 02:00:25,053
<i>Please be well until we return home.</i>

1130
02:00:25,196 --> 02:00:28,324
<i>And don't worry about Jin-seok.</i>

1131
02:00:28,532 --> 02:00:32,832
<i>I will definitely keep him safe.</i>

1132
02:00:33,470 --> 02:00:36,962
<i>Please say hello to Young-shin.
And tell her not to worry.</i>

1133
02:00:37,408 --> 02:00:40,343
<i>When I get discharged and return home...</i>

1134
02:00:40,644 --> 02:00:44,045
<i>I'll open a shoe store and make you
proud of me.</i>

1135
02:00:44,114 --> 02:00:46,947
<i>It's getting cold. Take care of yourself, Mom.</i>

1136
02:00:47,017 --> 02:00:51,147
<i>Until our family reunites,
please stay healthy.</i>

1137
02:01:46,443 --> 02:01:50,971
All these patients came from the battle
near the 38th parallel.

1138
02:01:51,048 --> 02:01:54,609
You are crazy to go back there.

1139
02:01:54,685 --> 02:01:57,449
How can you be sure
that you'll even find him?

1140
02:01:57,521 --> 02:02:02,254
You'll be discharged in a week.
Think about your mom!

1141
02:02:02,326 --> 02:02:04,521
For God's sake, listen to me.

1142
02:02:04,595 --> 02:02:05,960
See you soon.

1143
02:02:06,030 --> 02:02:09,693
Think of Young-shin's brother and sisters.

1144
02:02:09,767 --> 02:02:11,826
Jin-seok! Private Lee!

1145
02:02:14,705 --> 02:02:16,866
Take care, you bastard.

1146
02:02:29,453 --> 02:02:34,186
We'll attack up the middle
of hills 931 and 851, diverting the enemy.

1147
02:02:34,258 --> 02:02:36,783
Once the artillery attack ends...

1148
02:02:36,960 --> 02:02:41,727
1st and 2nd Battalion will flank
the hills from both directions.

1149
02:02:42,366 --> 02:02:47,065
We have to take out Flag Unit...

1150
02:02:47,137 --> 02:02:49,162
at all costs.

1151
02:02:49,239 --> 02:02:52,470
Don't forget we've modified
our operation plan. Any questions?

1152
02:02:52,543 --> 02:02:54,306
When will PFC Lee join the mission?

1153
02:02:54,378 --> 02:02:56,278
His mission has been canceled.

1154
02:02:56,347 --> 02:03:01,114
Since the Americans moved
the attack up 24 hours, there's no time.

1155
02:03:01,185 --> 02:03:04,177
Instead, we'll have him speak
over the microphone.

1156
02:03:07,091 --> 02:03:09,150
- Sir.
- What is it?

1157
02:03:09,226 --> 02:03:11,251
I'm PFC Lee, Lee Jin-tae's brother.

1158
02:03:11,328 --> 02:03:13,922
It's an honor to meet
the brother of the traitor.

1159
02:03:13,997 --> 02:03:17,524
Unless he sees me, he won't believe me.
Please let me join the mission.

1160
02:03:17,601 --> 02:03:21,594
We start the attack in an hour.
There's not enough time.

1161
02:03:21,672 --> 02:03:25,267
If he sees that I am alive,
he'll come back for sure.

1162
02:03:25,342 --> 02:03:27,071
Out of the question!

1163
02:03:27,144 --> 02:03:30,341
Sir, please.

1164
02:03:30,414 --> 02:03:31,938
Answer me one question:

1165
02:03:32,015 --> 02:03:34,848
Is this for your country or your brother?

1166
02:03:35,519 --> 02:03:37,749
Just read the script over the speaker.

1167
02:03:40,924 --> 02:03:42,551
<i>Forty minutes to go!</i>

1168
02:03:42,626 --> 02:03:46,426
<i>No enemy movements detected, sir!</i>

1169
02:03:46,497 --> 02:03:51,491
<i>F- 86 Sabres are standing by.
Artillery units are standing by.</i>

1170
02:03:53,404 --> 02:03:57,864
- Where is the script?
- It hasn't been delivered yet.

1171
02:03:58,275 --> 02:03:59,867
Wait a moment.

1172
02:04:06,483 --> 02:04:11,250
Check personal arms, daggers,
grenades and extra ammunition!

1173
02:04:38,782 --> 02:04:41,717
Sir, PFC Lee is running towards the enemy.

1174
02:04:54,498 --> 02:04:55,863
What's going on?

1175
02:04:55,933 --> 02:05:00,029
- He just surrendered.
- What? Surrendered?

1176
02:05:02,940 --> 02:05:05,875
If you're lying, you're dead.
Why are you here?

1177
02:05:05,943 --> 02:05:10,039
I came here to see my brother,
the leader of Flag Unit.

1178
02:05:10,113 --> 02:05:12,308
- What?
- Please let me see him.

1179
02:05:12,683 --> 02:05:16,585
I'll kill you if you're lying. Check it out!

1180
02:05:16,820 --> 02:05:20,847
A yellow dog is here saying
he's the brother of Mother Owl.

1181
02:05:20,924 --> 02:05:22,721
Confirm.

1182
02:05:22,793 --> 02:05:25,819
Let me talk to him!
He doesn't know I'm alive!

1183
02:05:25,896 --> 02:05:27,056
Shut up!

1184
02:05:27,130 --> 02:05:30,293
Negative. He says his brother is dead.

1185
02:05:30,367 --> 02:05:35,361
Please, let me talk to him.
Jin-tae, it's me, Jin-seok!

1186
02:05:36,507 --> 02:05:41,001
You're a damn spy. What's your mission?

1187
02:05:41,378 --> 02:05:44,677
Spit it out before I blow your head off.

1188
02:05:44,748 --> 02:05:47,808
Let me talk to him. He'll know it's me!

1189
02:05:47,885 --> 02:05:49,113
Stop screwing with me!

1190
02:05:49,186 --> 02:05:51,518
- I'm begging you!
- What are you here for?

1191
02:05:51,588 --> 02:05:54,352
- Please let me talk to him!
- Speak up!

1192
02:05:54,424 --> 02:05:55,618
I'm begging you.

1193
02:05:55,692 --> 02:06:00,493
Sir, we've got an order to bring him
to the security unit.

1194
02:06:03,033 --> 02:06:04,796
Get him out of here!

1195
02:06:06,069 --> 02:06:09,800
<i>Fellow comrades, it has been
several months since the attack began.</i>

1196
02:06:09,873 --> 02:06:13,707
<i>Our military is still overpowering
the South. The total death toll...</i>

1197
02:06:13,777 --> 02:06:17,042
- How far away is Flag Unit?
- Ask the security unit!

1198
02:06:18,649 --> 02:06:22,085
<i>The growing numbers of informants
will only result in more innocent deaths.</i>

1199
02:06:22,152 --> 02:06:26,816
Incoming! Air attack! Air attack!

1200
02:07:13,904 --> 02:07:16,771
- Hurry up, let's go.
- You're goddamn crazy!

1201
02:09:19,596 --> 02:09:21,757
Where is Flag Unit?

1202
02:09:32,843 --> 02:09:36,176
Attack! Attack!

1203
02:09:51,828 --> 02:09:53,625
Where the hell are you going?

1204
02:09:54,931 --> 02:09:56,865
He's a dog from the South!

1205
02:10:58,428 --> 02:11:00,230
It's Flag Unit! It's Flag Unit!

1206
02:11:00,230 --> 02:11:01,697
It's Flag Unit! It's Flag Unit!

1207
02:13:12,562 --> 02:13:13,961
Jin-tae.

1208
02:13:23,239 --> 02:13:26,265
You Southern bastard, die!

1209
02:13:26,343 --> 02:13:31,144
It's Jin-seok. It's Jin-seok! Snap out of it!

1210
02:13:31,214 --> 02:13:33,682
- I'll kill you all!
- Jin-tae.

1211
02:14:08,218 --> 02:14:10,482
Jin-tae, please. Please.

1212
02:14:34,511 --> 02:14:36,001
Jin-tae!

1213
02:15:26,362 --> 02:15:31,265
You Southern piece of shit.
You piece of shit!

1214
02:15:31,501 --> 02:15:34,231
Jin-tae, please.

1215
02:15:34,838 --> 02:15:37,466
Come to your senses!

1216
02:15:37,540 --> 02:15:40,907
Look at me.
I am Jin-seok, your only brother.

1217
02:15:42,078 --> 02:15:46,777
- I'm your brother!
- I'll kill all you bastards!

1218
02:15:47,117 --> 02:15:50,416
Retreat! Retreat!

1219
02:15:50,487 --> 02:15:51,852
Retreat!

1220
02:16:21,084 --> 02:16:23,951
Jin-tae, get up. Get up.

1221
02:16:29,759 --> 02:16:33,718
We have to go. We have to go now!

1222
02:16:34,764 --> 02:16:36,664
Let's go. We have no time!

1223
02:16:38,568 --> 02:16:41,560
Get up. We have to go.

1224
02:16:41,671 --> 02:16:44,435
We have to get out of here.

1225
02:16:44,507 --> 02:16:47,237
Please, get up!

1226
02:16:50,013 --> 02:16:53,210
Don't you want to go home and see Mom?

1227
02:16:56,886 --> 02:17:00,913
You have to visit Young-shin's grave.

1228
02:17:03,526 --> 02:17:07,462
What about the shoe store
and making Mom proud?

1229
02:17:07,530 --> 02:17:10,397
You can't die here!

1230
02:17:10,466 --> 02:17:15,426
You worked your ass off
just so I could go to school.

1231
02:17:15,505 --> 02:17:19,965
You have to live to see me
go to college. Come on!

1232
02:17:25,481 --> 02:17:29,315
- Jin-seok?
- Jin-tae.

1233
02:17:30,320 --> 02:17:32,720
You're really alive?

1234
02:17:45,468 --> 02:17:46,594
Go!

1235
02:17:47,870 --> 02:17:50,236
I won't go alone.

1236
02:17:50,306 --> 02:17:52,103
Just go.

1237
02:17:52,175 --> 02:17:53,301
No way!

1238
02:17:53,376 --> 02:17:55,776
Get up and come with me!

1239
02:17:55,845 --> 02:18:00,407
Listen, I will surrender
and come home after the war.

1240
02:18:00,950 --> 02:18:04,010
I've been making your shoes for college.

1241
02:18:04,187 --> 02:18:08,385
I haven't finished them, so I won't die.
Now, go!

1242
02:18:10,760 --> 02:18:13,854
- I won't!
- I'm okay.

1243
02:18:13,930 --> 02:18:17,798
Do as I tell you. Go!

1244
02:18:17,867 --> 02:18:20,358
- I won't go without you!
- Then we'll both die!

1245
02:18:20,436 --> 02:18:23,530
- No!
- Listen to me!

1246
02:18:25,708 --> 02:18:28,541
Look at me. Trust me.

1247
02:18:35,385 --> 02:18:37,114
I found this after the fire.

1248
02:18:42,125 --> 02:18:44,525
Give it to me...

1249
02:18:46,296 --> 02:18:49,197
when you see me again.

1250
02:18:50,466 --> 02:18:52,991
You have to come back.

1251
02:18:53,736 --> 02:18:55,863
You have to come back.

1252
02:21:30,860 --> 02:21:32,384
You promised...

1253
02:21:33,596 --> 02:21:36,531
to come back and finish the shoes.

1254
02:21:38,768 --> 02:21:40,998
But what are you doing here?

1255
02:21:45,241 --> 02:21:47,471
I've waited for so long.

1256
02:21:49,512 --> 02:21:53,414
What happened to your promise?

1257
02:21:55,351 --> 02:21:57,444
Say something!

1258
02:22:00,189 --> 02:22:03,124
I've been waiting to see you for 50 years.

1259
02:22:03,626 --> 02:22:07,187
Please say something.

1260
02:22:10,733 --> 02:22:14,225
I shouldn't have left you alone back then.

1261
02:22:16,305 --> 02:22:17,704
Jin-tae.

1262
02:22:19,175 --> 02:22:20,608
Jin-tae!

1263
02:23:28,010 --> 02:23:29,477
Jin-seok!

1264
02:23:31,013 --> 02:23:32,378
Jin-seok!

1265
02:24:15,458 --> 02:24:18,825
Let's go get some water.

1266
02:24:29,005 --> 02:24:33,533
How have you been? You all got so big.

1267
02:24:34,276 --> 02:24:37,177
We are going back to school, you know.

1268
02:24:37,246 --> 02:24:38,235
Really?

1269
02:24:38,848 --> 02:24:42,579
I want to go to school, too. How about you?

1270
02:24:42,652 --> 02:24:45,780
<i>Of course I do.</i>

1271
